unctional magnetic resonance imaging in order to observe differences in brain activity between talented and untalented individuals during the performance of phonetic tasks (perception of phonetic differences, imitation, reading).  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 17. Dez 2021) 0aNeurolinguistics. 0aPhonetics. 0aSecond language acquisitionxPhysiological aspects. 4aNeurolinguistik. 4aPhonetik. 4aSpracherwerb. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Linguistics / General.2bisacsh  aLanguage Acquisition.  aLanguage Talent.  aNeurolinguistics.  aPhonetics.1 aAckermann, Hermann, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAnufryk, Volha, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBaumotte, Henrike, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBrendel, Bettina, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDogil, Grzegorz, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDogil, Grzegorz, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aGrodd, Wolfgang, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHu, Xiaochen, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJilka, Matthias, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKumar, Vinod, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLewandowski, Natalie, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNardo, Davide, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aReiterer, Susanne Maria, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aReiterer, Susanne Maria, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aRota, Giuseppina, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWildgruber,